<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a0fbfc3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6518"><num value="6518">§ 6518.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is authorized to be appropriated $660,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2019 through 2023 to carry out—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a0fbfc4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6518/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> activities authorized by this subchapter; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a0fbfc5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6518/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> other hazardous fuel reduction activities of the Secretary, including making grants to States, local governments, Indian tribes, and other eligible recipients for activities authorized by law.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a0fbfc6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/148/tI/s108">Pub. L. 108–148, title I, § 108</ref>, <date date="2003-12-03">Dec. 3, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/1901">117 Stat. 1901</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/115/334/tVIII/s8402">Pub. L. 115–334, title VIII, § 8402</ref>, <date date="2018-12-20">Dec. 20, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4841">132 Stat. 4841</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
